<subSubSection id="C362D9F0E80751347D6AF83F3E91FED2" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC78A7BE80751347D6AF83F3E91FED2" blockId="7.[828,1436,2027,2082]" lastBlockId="8.[151,760,190,373]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7D6AF83F3CFFF7E5" bold="true" box="[828,958,2027,2050]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Comments.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C78F1F8E807513B7AAAF83F3ADDF7E5" box="[1276,1436,2027,2050]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pselaphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tianmuensis">
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7AAAF83F3A4DF7E5" box="[1276,1292,2027,2050]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90C5669E807513B7B4BF83F3ADDF7E5" box="[1309,1436,2027,2050]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">tianmuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group and differs from related species primarily in the relatively elongate median lobe of aedeagus. The single male from 
<collectingCountry id="F36FCAEBE80851347F1AFF0A3EC1FF12" box="[332,384,222,245]" name="Laos" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Laos</collectingCountry>
is morphologically largely identical to those of Hainan, even the positions of the two endophalic sclerites are almost the same.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
